In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims March 2019 as Irish-American Heritage Month. He highlights the significant contributions Irish Americans have made throughout American history, including their involvement in the Revolutionary War and their role in shaping the principles of self-government outlined in the Declaration of Independence and the Constitution. The article also mentions the perseverance and success of Irish Americans, despite facing discrimination and poverty. It acknowledges the achievements of notable Irish Americans, such as Edmund McIlhenny, the creator of Tabasco hot sauce, and Andrew Mellon, a businessman and Secretary of the Treasury. The article concludes by calling upon all Americans to celebrate the achievements of Irish Americans and their contributions to the nation.